review_blob: A very nice beer with. A mild flavor. That slight smoke is not overpowering. I think it is a better choice in a half pint. As opposed to a pint. Nice caramel beginning. And great color.
Anis! I was really excited to taste this beer and then I realized it was mostly anis. Love dark, stout, imperial stout, etc, but this was overpowered by the black licorice flavor.

By far the best beer that is offered currently at this brewery. Right from the tap, offered on a flight of 4 has a great balance of flavor and hop. Nice color that is nice full flavor that contains a full taste. I could go back to other IPAS offered there after drinking this complete beer.

Wow. It has been a while since a stout has stopped me in my tracks. Great from start to finish. Everything you want from a boozy barrel aged stout. Incredible round taste from top to bottom, beginning to end. Beautiful, rich black color. Chocolate, taste. Get it.

I bit to much bitter at the start of the taste for me to really enjoy the stout aspect of this beer. It does have a nice taste and smoother taste at the back end, yet it still lacks that full body flavor. Pours black. slight head.
The last on tap serving at Thrash zone. A nice Belgium style beer with a nice dark color and a sweet finish. Lacks a lot of the real end of a truest great Belgium beer but it will do in a fix.

On tap at Thrash Zone in Yokohama. Great beer by the way. Nice light brown color. Easy foam top. Taste is of wheat, nutty, bitter finish. Not really much to the taste for me. I enjoy stone brewery, yet this is not. Hit for me. Its an IPA though.

Just returned from living in Belgium for three years. This beer is a great reminder of what Im missing in Europe. It is the best Belgium American Beer I have had since leaving Belgium. It says quadruple but it taste like a triple. So yummy.
Drink this beer! After trying IPA after IPA in Japan I finally found one worth noting. Delicious, hearty, and worthy. It is poured by the brew master himself.
beer_name: Thrashzone Brew Labo Speed Kills IPA

review_blob: Dark rich pour with a nice dark foam. Chocolate & coffee smell. A nice full filling taste. Is a little thick and partly oily. Almost a hint if a black IPA it so hoppy.
A nice mild black IPA . This was a stand out at the Antwerp Beer Passion 2013. Has a slight foam. Great taste from start to finish.

Almost a little too harsh up front for not a much depth.mat the end. This has a great chocolate, coffee taste but is out done by an unwanted bitterness. Pours black with a light foam. Over a little too bitter for me in the style of Mikkeller .
False flat as far as drinking a good stout. Bland. A typical Belgium stout. No depth, taste, or after taste.
This is a stout that is perfectly married to a black IPA. You can taste both. The black IPA at the start then a real stout at the end. Beautiful!
Fantastic stout. Just purchased at Moeder Lambic in Brussels. They just arrived. In line with most stouts. Has a light foam but is rich in taste.

I feel this beer should be classified as a dark IPA. It has a light flavor, medium bitterness, creamy texture, long bitter finish. Toasted malt. Possesses a nice small foam all the way down to the last drink.

I first had this beer at the Beer Passion weekend in Antwerp. It caught my attention as a good beer. I return to it when I want something a bit better than the normal pils or bland belgium blonde. This is a very subtle triple. .75 bottle An amber color, foam that disappears quickly.floral, citrus, medium body, creamy.

A black stout that taste incredible for having such a high alcohol percentage. A unique taste that starts smooth and ends with a berry flavor. Nice that it isnt oily or thick on the tongue. Almost no head. It cost me 12 EURO but had to try it since Im a Mikkeller, Nogne-O, and a Brew Dog fan. An overall superb collaboration. Still not sure if I want to pay that price again, but would like to drink it again.
beer_name: BrewDog / Ngne  / Mikkeller Black Tokyo* Horizon

review_blob: I love a great stout and I love Irish whiskey. This beer is a perfect marriage. Hardly any bitter of the stout but contains a great balance of sweet taste. Had this from bottle right after drinking the Regular Celebration stout at Delirium cafe in Brussels. Awesome.

Yes it officially qualifies as a Trappist beer so they have that pedigree. Beside that it is a good beer. Nice color, smooth taste. Nicest flavor is at the end. Glad to have tried it. At the lower end of the Trappist list for me.

Pours like a regular Stille Nacht beer. A slightly darker color than the original. I must say this IS my Christmas beer of choice. I have had their latest Reserve and I found this to be a tolerable version of the product. It was much more sour than the regular Stille Nacht, but packed with intensity. Bought it at The Kulminator in Antwerp in 2014 so it may have aged well.
beer_name: De Dolle Stille Nacht Special Reserva 2005

review_blob: .750 bottle. Pours dark in color with almost no head. Has an aged smell almost like wine and port. Reminds me of aged cognac anding with a nice raisin taste. It is a very pleasant beer to enjoy.

So Mikkeller, so good. This pours so thick and black out of the bottle with a slight and quick vanishing head. Smells like wine, port, oak. Almost feels a bit oily on the tongue. The first taste is of a intense chocolate then coffee roast, raisins. Smooth and tasty all the way down. Hardly any bitter taste.

When I drank this Christmas beer last November I new it was something special. It is possesses the distinct Oerbier flavor typical to the De Dolle brewery however this one possesses that perfect combination. It tastes like an aged beer right out of the bottle of the same year. Drinks like a fine wine. Amber color that starts with a grape/wine flavor then ends with a slightly sour finish. SO Good!

A solid blend of rich bitter chocolate, great tasting coffee, sweet malt, oats, and overall goodness. It pours black and thick and its intense. Has a hint of fruit at the end. One of the best Coffee/Beer combos around.

Black in color but more of a dark beer rather than a black beer. Not a stout beer by American standards. Pours with a slight foam. Complex flavor- citrus, malts, caramel with slight chocolate with a nice bitterness at the end.
Immediate dark chocolate (bitter) taste. Very rich in flavor. Dies down at the end.
